Next, we estimate the background variance in feature density (V) using the 75th percentile oscillation distance from an ordered list of increase / decrease distances observed when traversing the histogram. The estimated background and upper/lower variance from background are drawn as green lines on the histogram. The colocation peak height (H) is maximum histogram value above the upper variance level. AMI is the integral of histogram values above the upper variance level. BMI is calculated to quantify anti colocation and is the integral of histogram values below the lower variance level.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
